  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nFeature\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\nContext is explicitly defined and consumed by providers and consumers.\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\nGeneral purpose context which is provided by default at the root level. It could function as a container for config or application dependencies.\r\n\r\nThe syntax example below hasn't be heavily considered but generally illustrates the feature request.\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst globalContext = {\r\n    value: 'something',\r\n    fetchSomething: () => fetch('https://some.thing')\r\n}\r\n\r\nReactDOM.render(<App />, element, globalContext)\r\n```\r\nThen consume it with something like\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst Toolbar = () => {\r\n    const globalContext = useGlobalContext()\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
